<paragraph blockId="18.[189,1399,311,443]" pageId="18" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hincks" authorityYear="1861" box="[189,414,311,337]" class="Hydrozoa" family="Haleciidae" genus="Halecium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leptothecata" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="tenellum">
<emphasis box="[189,414,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="67">Halecium tenellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a nearly cosmopolitan species (
<bibRefCitation author="Cornelius P. F. S." box="[833,1021,311,338]" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" pagination="375 - 426" refId="ref20966" refString="Cornelius P. F. S. 1975. A revision of the species of Lafoeidae and Haleciidae (Coelenterata: Hydroida) recorded from Britain and nearby seas. Bulletin of the British Museum Natural History. Zoology 28: 375 - 426. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / p. 271711" type="journal article" year="1975">Cornelius 1975</bibRefCitation>
), with records from all oceans, including polar waters, although some identifications from high latitudes in the North Atlantic proved to be erroneous (
<bibRefCitation author="Calder D. R." box="[397,550,381,407]" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 140" refId="ref20172" refString="Calder D. R. 1991. Shallow-water hydroids of Bermuda. The Thecatae, exclusive of Plumularioidea. Life Sciences Contributions of the Royal Ontario Museum 154: 1 - 140." type="journal article" year="1991">Calder 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuchert P." box="[566,758,381,408]" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" pagination="607 - 639" refId="ref25409" refString="Schuchert P. 2005. Taxonomic revision and systematic notes on some Halecium species (Cnidaria, Hydrozoa). Journal of Natural History 39 (8): 607 - 639. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930400001319" type="journal article" year="2005">Schuchert 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[968,1121,381,407]" name="South Africa" pageId="18" pageNumber="67">South Africa</collectingCountry>
by Millard (1975). Its bathymetric range extends from the intertidal zone to 
<quantity box="[809,897,416,443]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pena Cantero A. L. &amp; Garcia Carrascosa A. M." box="[911,1387,416,442]" pageId="18" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 180" refId="ref24277" refString="Pena Cantero A. L. &amp; Garcia Carrascosa A. M. 2002. The benthic hydroid fauna of the Chafarinas Islands (Alboran Sea, western Mediterranean). Zoologische Verhandelingen, Leiden 337: 1 - 180." type="journal article" year="2002">Peña Cantero &amp; García Carrascosa 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
